caption:
Unveiling our New & Improved Raja Park Branch – Jaipur
 
In our pursuit to constantly elevate our customer's banking experience, we have relocated our Raja Park branch in Jaipur, Rajasthan, to a brand new location. This move not only enhances accessibility but also signifies our commitment to serving you better.
 
With the relocation of the Raja Park branch, our footprint now spans across Rajasthan, boasting 48 branches in the state, with a noteworthy 10 in the Pink City of India – Jaipur. Among these, 29 branches are unbanked rural centres, serving the unserved and making banking accessible to all.
 
In a gala ceremony, the new branch was inaugurated by @drkailashvermabjp, MLA Bagru (Ex-Minister of State, Govt. of Rajasthan), and other distinguished guests and senior bank officials.
 
Our new branch boasts state-of-the-art facilities and is staffed with a dedicated team of professionals ready to assist our customers with a broad array of banking services.

Beyond Banking: Jana Bank's Humanitarian Touch at @ankitgram_ngo, Ujjain

In our pursuit of creating positive transformations beyond banking, Jana Bank embarked on a heartfelt journey at Sewadham Ashram, Ujjain. 

Guided by the ethos of compassion, we, in the esteemed presence of Shri Sudhir Bhai Goyal, Founder-Director of the Ashram, and Mr. Shrinivas Murty, President, Branch Banking & Marketing extended our support by providing critical medical equipment to the 750+ residents. By providing these essential medical devices, we are not just fulfilling a requirement; we are enhancing the overall well-being and dignity of the residents at Sewadham Ashram. 

Established by *Shri Sudhir Bhai Goyal, Sewadham Ashram stands as a symbol of compassion and a beacon of hope, embracing those who are often left forgotten and vulnerable in our society. He has been instrumental in running the Ashram since the age of 13, building it on the principle of Manav Sewa – Madhav Sewa i.e. Service to Humanity is Service to God.

#JanaBankCares #CommunityImpact #CSRJourney #MakeADifference

alt: Photo by Jana Small Finance Bank Ltd on December 06, 2023. May be an image of money, card, banner, water filter, balloon and office.
caption:
We are happy to share the glimpses of yet another successful CSR initiative at Moyna Adarsha Sikshyatan School Arankiyarana,in Kumirda village, West Bengal. This endeavour involved the installation of a critically needed RO Drinking Water Purifier, officially inaugurated by the esteemed Mr. Biman Panda, Village Panchayat Pradhan. 
 
Situated in an economically disadvantaged area, this school had been grappling with inadequate water facilities, adversely affecting over 2000 students hailing from low-income families. The implementation of this CSR initiative ensures access to clean drinking water, garnering heartfelt blessings from students, their families and teachers alike.

#JanaCares #Impact #CleanWaterForAll #DrinkingWater #SocialResponsibility #PositiveChange

alt: Photo by Jana Small Finance Bank Ltd on December 04, 2023. May be an image of cash machine, banner, hamper, water filter, poster and office.
caption:
Bringing Clean Drinking Water to Solapur's Young Minds

Jana SFB is truly grateful for the opportunity to serve the community through its recent CSR initiative at the Progressive Educational Society's High School in #Solapur, #Maharashtra. By installing a state-of-the-art RO Drinking Water Purification machinery, we have taken a small step to facilitate over 3000 underprivileged students with access to clean & safe drinking water.

This effort, not only addresses the basic necessity of clean drinking water but also contributes significantly to the overall well-being and development of the community. We are not just providing water; we are nurturing a foundation for a healthier, happier, and more empowered Solapur.

#JanaCares #Impact #CleanWaterForAll #DrinkingWater #SocialResponsibility #PositiveChange

alt: Photo by Jana Small Finance Bank Ltd on November 22, 2023.
caption:
In an effort to build a cleaner and more sustainable future for the residents of Guwahati, Assam, Jana SFB recently donated an Automated Tipper Van to Guwahati Municipal Corporation.
 
The Handing Over Ceremony, held in the esteemed presence of Shri. Megha Nidhi Dahal, IAS, Commissioner of Guwahati Municipal Corporation, and Shri. Mrigen Saraniya, Mayor of Guwahati, marked a significant milestone for our CSR efforts.
 
Our CSR initiative in Guwahati aligns with our broader vision of being a catalyst for positive change, not just in the banking sector but also in the communities we are privileged to be a part of.
 
#CSRInitiative #CleanerGuwahati #CommunityEngagement #JanaCares

alt: Photo by Jana Small Finance Bank Ltd on November 28, 2023.
caption:
In our ongoing mission to make a meaningful difference, Jana Small Finance Bank has extended its hand towards brightening the educational journey of young minds at Government Senior Secondary and Upper Primary School in Kotputli, #Rajasthan, by providing the students of both schools with seating benches, cutting-edge computer systems, and a state-of-the-art water purifier.
 

These essentials go beyond mere objects – they are instruments of empowerment, transforming learning spaces into nurturing environments that foster growth and creativity. We firmly believe that empowering the younger generations of our country is not just a responsibility but a privilege. By enhancing their learning environment, we are sowing the seeds of a brighter tomorrow.

#Janacsr #Education #Empowerment #YoungMinds #educationforall

firstComment:
@suryodaybank It's easy to make 15 friends in one year but keeping one friend for 15 years is special...🤝🤝❤️❤️My friend @modestmanisha03 is more like a sister than a friend..
The incident which is close to my heart is  when we were in class 5th and I and my friend was sitting with me in the same seat and my friend cracked the joke during the class..I could not control my laughter and I laughed out aloud...My friend however controlled her laughter...My teacher saw me laughing and called me, she scolded me and said me to stand outside the class for one hour..My friend couldn't see this and she stood up and said to the teacher that it was her fault also as she cracked the joke and so she should punish her also..My teacher punished both of us...This was the first time, my friend supported me, took a stand for me .. .Since then, whenever I'm in trouble, I see her standing next to me .No matter what the problem is, she has the solution for it..That day my friend said to me outside the class during the punishment that- "No matter the day is bright or dark, I will always hold your hand and support you, without ever judging you" ..Till now, she remembers her promise and supports and motivates me, whenever I need her..❤️❤️... She makes me laugh at that moment when I think that I could not even smile..😊..She has taught me to handle all problems and situations boldly and bravely..She has taught me to enjoy life's each and every moment😍.. Friend like her is worth more than a diamond..When I count my blessings, I count her twice..❤️❤️ #bankofsmiles #suryodaybank #friends

In our commitment to making a positive impact on the communities we serve, we reached Chandigarh, known for its well-planned urban infrastructure and also for its efforts towards animal welfare initiatives.

Major Jacob, his team and his organization CLAW are a boon to India and the world. A huge applause for Team CLAW from USA 🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸
As a proud citizen of USA, a nation built on the deeply spiritual principles of Life, Liberty and the Pursuit of Happiness, I absolutely love CLAW, their long term vision and their different programs - Lifeskills and Mindset Training courses like GRIT, their treks, river rafting expeditions, bike expeditions, Skill and Endurance challenge competitions like Soul of Steel and so many others. This organization has a HUGE heart and seems to be adept at doing great things very quietly. For example, if someone shows highest merit/talent for any of their programs like Soul of Steel (SOS) but doesn’t have the funds to pay the fees, CLAW takes genuine interest in meritorious candidates and does everything they can to fund such people out of their own profits. They don’t seem to clamor for publicity in the name of charity or DE&I and they seem to have great interest in going about their good deeds in a very dignified way. 
What I love most about CLAW is - They are very simple people. They excel in actions. The content, planning, execution for each of their programs is top notch. But if you talk to them, they’ll make you feel like you are the smart one. Ha ha 🙂🙂
Ms. Gul Panag has earned my lifelong respect by participating with CLAW. 
USA sends CLAW its very best wishes
🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸❤❤❤🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸

latestComments/3/text: In order to fulfill the resolution of being fit and make more wealth to fulfill personal goals, l forget to nature myself and think about my mental health to only run in the race of my resolutions. With so much tension and pressure, I may have achieved those resolutions but something long medicals bills and other mental issues took a toll at me, so this year I am taking a resolution to took after my mental health more without bothering about other things in life. The materialistic demands in life will never end I have understand that life is all about giving which will make sure that we stop complaining for not conquering personal milestones.  I'll start with small things of making a small shelter house for the stray dogs in my house and in area around me to protect them from extreme heat, cold and rain because ultimately we all love the imported breeds and in pursuit of that, we forget the beautiful Indian stray dogs who are always guiding our home and our street. I'll ensure that they also get food in those shelters so they don't need to find food from the leftovers and the garbage on the street. firstComment:
The carefree days of summer vacation
.
Summer vacation was a time of endless possibilities and boundless joy. I remember waking up to the warm sun streaming through my window, the birds chirping merrily outside, and the anticipation of a day filled with adventure. I would spend hours exploring the neighborhood, building forts in the woods, playing tag with my friends, and swimming in the local creek. The days seemed to stretch on forever, and every moment was filled with laughter and excitement.
.
